728
00:33:54,133 --> 00:33:55,734
-How dare you say that?
-Sorry.

729
00:33:56,168 --> 00:33:57,569
-I lied.
-Why?

730
00:33:57,636 --> 00:33:58,971
Is this the mouth that lied?

731
00:34:00,005 --> 00:34:02,007
-It was just a joke.
-Did this mouth lie?

732
00:34:02,074 --> 00:34:04,209
-It was a joke.
-It was this mouth, right?

733
00:34:09,815 --> 00:34:10,816
Directly?

734
00:34:12,084 --> 00:34:13,018
Directly?

735
00:34:15,854 --> 00:34:17,322
Really. My jaw will fall out.

736
00:34:31,703 --> 00:34:32,905
You had to say it.

737
00:34:34,706 --> 00:34:35,974
But it hurts.

738
00:34:40,446 --> 00:34:41,713
It really hurts.

739
00:34:43,382 --> 00:34:44,283
Looks like Hannya.

740
00:34:44,349 --> 00:34:45,851
-Seriously?
-Seriously.

741
00:34:49,154 --> 00:34:50,823
-Was it that bad?
-It was.

742
00:34:51,390 --> 00:34:52,858
With a little more force...

743
00:34:53,192 --> 00:34:55,194
-One more jerk?
-It would've fallen off.

744
00:34:55,427 --> 00:34:57,496
-You mean dislocated?
-I mean ripped out.

745
00:34:57,896 --> 00:34:58,997
Like in The Mask?

746
00:34:59,164 --> 00:35:00,933
-The movie?
-The film The Mask.

747
00:35:01,066 --> 00:35:04,736
But if your jaw bounced back,
what would be the first thing you say?

748
00:35:04,803 --> 00:35:06,772
-I wonder.
-What would you say?

749
00:35:06,939 --> 00:35:08,340
It stretches a meter, right?

750
00:35:08,407 --> 00:35:11,777
