"I love you" to "sizzle."

833
00:42:26,378 --> 00:42:27,946
I think it's the perfect sound.

834
00:42:28,246 --> 00:42:30,448
That must have come close.

835
00:42:31,516 --> 00:42:34,819
-It's amazing how you kept straight faces.
-But it sure was funny.

836
00:42:34,920 --> 00:42:36,288
You endured it well.

837
00:42:36,354 --> 00:42:38,123
It suddenly sounded like home.

838
00:42:38,189 --> 00:42:40,625
-Suddenly it sounded homey.
-All in one "sizzle."

839
00:42:40,692 --> 00:42:43,194
-We couldn't be further away.
-So homey.

840
00:42:47,565 --> 00:42:49,501
Let's go.

841
00:42:52,904 --> 00:42:54,673
Maybe that's why he went ahead.

842
00:42:55,540 --> 00:42:58,076
He's doing that thing. I bet you.

843
00:42:58,343 --> 00:43:00,378
-He must be.
-He is.

844
00:43:00,812 --> 00:43:02,647
Kukky, wait. I don't want it.

845
00:43:08,186 --> 00:43:09,788
This is bad.

846
00:43:10,288 --> 00:43:11,723
Really bad.

847
00:43:17,729 --> 00:43:19,064
